SISTER ELLA vied three to two wide, entered the lane in the four path as an outer rival offered a bid, but was outkicked and tired between horses. IUKA MISS pursued off of the pace two wide and between horses, then three wide around the turn and ran on evenly among foes. SPIRITUAL LADY bobbled slightly at the start, set the pace inside of vying rivals, sparred with an outer foe around the turn, got headed by that one and a wider bidder entering the lane and weakened through the final furlong. MYDIXIELANDDELIGHT lacked speed three wide and between horses, retreated to trail turning for home and made little impact. WINDY WALK broke a step slow, laid off of the pace along the inside and failed to factor. MARCO SUNSET pressed four to three wide into the turn, but was floated four wide turning for home and weakened between horses. CONTRABBANDA prompted the pace two wide and between horses for a quarter mile, but failed to keep pace at the half mile pole and wilted around the turn.
